ds3PortAttribLbo.name: ds3PortAttribLbo
ds3PortAttribLbo.description: Line build out. Line build out (DS3 port) values Value Description 1 Cable length range from 0 to 225 feet. 2 Cable length range from 226 to 450 feet.

ds3PortAttribLineCde.name: ds3PortAttribLineCde
ds3PortAttribLineCde.description: DS3 line code. Valid value is B3ZS.

ds3PortAttribFmt.name: ds3PortAttribFmt
ds3PortAttribFmt.description: Frame format. Valid values are CBIT, M23 or UNFRAMED. For PDM3 unit, if the port type is DS3_ASYN_STS1, then <FMT> can be CBIT, M23 or UNFRAMED. If the port type is DS3_TMUX_DS1 or DS3_SRV_DS1, then the <FMT> only can be CBIT or M23.

ds3PortAttribTACC.name: ds3PortAttribTACC
ds3PortAttribTACC.description: Defines the DS3 port as a test access port with a selected unique TAP number.

ds3PortAttribLof2ais.name: ds3PortAttribLof2ais
ds3PortAttribLof2ais.description: The parameter is provisioned to determine whether or not to generate DS3 AIS for the DS3 LOF. The Valid value of this parameter is 'no' and 'yes'. PQT3/PQT3A/PQT3P/PQT3B units support this parameter.

ds3PortAttribSvtimer.name: ds3PortAttribSvtimer
ds3PortAttribSvtimer.description: Signal validation timer in minutes. Valid values are shown below. Value Description From 00-03 Signal validation timer in minutes. Only valid if auto in-service feature is supported. <SVTIMER> is a string, and format is: HH-MM. to 48-00 HH - Hour, it is an integer ranging from 0 to 48; MM - Minute, it is an integer ranging from 0 to 59. The longest time is 48 hours. Default is 00-03 (3 minutes).

ds3PortAttribPST.name: ds3PortAttribPST
ds3PortAttribPST.description: The primary state of the entity. Administrative State (PST) Definition IS Puts the entity in service. OOS Puts the entity out of service.

ds3PortAttribSST.name: ds3PortAttribSST
ds3PortAttribSST.description: The secondary state of the entity. Administrative State (PST) Definition. AINS Puts the entity in automatic in-service. MT Removes the entity from service for maintenance.

ds3LoopbackStatus.name: ds3LoopbackStatus
ds3LoopbackStatus.description: This variable represents the current state of the loopback on the DS3 interface. It contains information about loopbacks established by a manager and remotely from the far end.

ds3LoopbackTimeout.name: ds3LoopbackTimeout
ds3LoopbackTimeout.description: The remnant time that loop-back will be released.

ds3RemoteALWFELPBK.name: ds3RemoteALWFELPBK
ds3RemoteALWFELPBK.description: (Optional) Far-end loopback allowance attribute of the port. If it is enable, the automatic far-end loopbacks are allowed. It is either enable or disable. The system default is enable. The parameter type is ENABLE_DISABLE, which disables or enables an attribute.Automatic application of loopbacks originating from the far end can be initiated on the T3 ports of a PDM3 card.

ds1PortIndexSlotId.name: ds1PortIndexSlotId
ds1PortIndexSlotId.description: Slot number. This will indicate what is the slot of the object.

ds1PortIndexPortId.name: ds1PortIndexPortId
ds1PortIndexPortId.description: Port Number. This will indicate what is the Port of the object.For the Transmux unit this is the DS3 port number.And for other Ds1 units, it's the Ds1 port Number.

ds1PortIndexPath.name: ds1PortIndexPath
ds1PortIndexPath.description: Ds1 identifier of the Transmux unit .For DS1 in a Transmux unit, it is equivalent to DS1 port number of its Transmux unit. For other Ds1 units, It will be zero.

ds1PortAttribLbo.name: ds1PortAttribLbo
ds1PortAttribLbo.description: Line build out. Line build out (DS1 port) values Value Description 1 Cable length range from 0 to 131 feet. 2 Cable length range from 132 to 262 feet. 3 Cable length range from 263 to 393 feet. 4 Cable length range from 394 to 524 feet. 5 Cable length range from 525 to 655 feet.

ds1PortAttribLineCde.name: ds1PortAttribLineCde
ds1PortAttribLineCde.description: DS1 Line coding. Valid value is AMI or B8ZS. Default is B8ZS.

ds1PortAttribFmt.name: ds1PortAttribFmt
ds1PortAttribFmt.description: Frame format. Valid value is SF, ESF or UNFRAMED.

ds1PortAttribTACC.name: ds1PortAttribTACC
ds1PortAttribTACC.description: Defines the DS1/T1 port as a test access port with a selected unique TAP number.

ds1PortAttribLof2ais.name: ds1PortAttribLof2ais
ds1PortAttribLof2ais.description: The parameter is provisioned to determine whether or not to generate DS1 AIS for the DS1 LOF

ds1PortAttribSvtimer.description: Signal validation timer in minutes. Valid values are shown below. Value Description From 00-03 Signal validation timer in minutes. Only valid if auto in-service feature is supported. <SVTIMER> is a string, and format is: HH-MM. to 48-00 HH - Hour, it is an integer ranging from 0 to 48; MM - Minute, it is an integer ranging from 0 to 59. The longest time is 48 hours. Default is 00-03 (3 minutes).

ds1PortAttribPST.name: ds1PortAttribPST
ds1PortAttribPST.description: The primary state of the entity. Administrative State (PST) Definition IS Puts the entity in service. OOS Puts the entity out of service.

ds1PortAttribSST.name: ds1PortAttribSST
ds1PortAttribSST.description: The secondary state of the entity. Administrative State (PST) Definition. AINS Puts the entity in automatic in-service. MT Removes the entity from service for maintenance.

ds1LoopbackStatus.name: ds1LoopbackStatus
ds1LoopbackStatus.description: This variable represents the current state of the loopback on the DS1 interface. It contains information about loopbacks established by a manager and remotely from the far end.

ds1LoopbackTimeout.name: ds1LoopbackTimeout
ds1LoopbackTimeout.description: The remnant time that loop-back will be released.

ds1RemoteALWFELPBK.name: ds1RemoteALWFELPBK
ds1RemoteALWFELPBK.description: (Optional) Far-end loopback allowance attribute of the port. If it is enable, the automatic far-end loopbacks are allowed. It is either enable or disable. The system default is enable. The parameter type is ENABLE_DISABLE, which disables or enables an attribute.Automatic application of loopbacks originating from the far end can be initiated on the T1 ports of a PLT1,PDT1,PDT1P card.It indicates that the port not support this parameter when the attribute is invalid.

ds1PortLpbkAutomaticTime.name: ds1PortLpbkAutomaticTime
ds1PortLpbkAutomaticTime.description: Time-out ticks (1 minute). For the T1 port default value is 120 (2 hours). 0 means time-out function is disabling. Valid values are 0~9999.

portType.name: portType
portType.description: The AID unit port type.Valid values are shown below. INTFTYPE values Value Description DS3_ASYN_STS1 DS3 signal asynchronous mapped into STS1. Default for DS3 unit. DS3_TMUX_DS1 Multiplexing and de-multiplexing of DS1s to/from DS3. Default for Transmux unit (PDM3). DS1_ASYN_VT1 DS1 signal asynchronous mapped into VT1. Default for DS1 unit. DS3_SRV_DS1 Multiplexing and de-multiplexing of DS1s to/from DS3 as M13 server. EC1 EC1 signal mapped into STS1. PQT3A support EC1 service. UAS It indicates there is no use of the port.
